<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="190" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[113,1089,1227,1474]" pageId="7" pageNumber="190">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[113,223,1227,1250]" pageId="7" pageNumber="190">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="WRANIK W." box="[227,436,1227,1250]" pageId="7" pageNumber="190" refId="ref17108" refString="WRANIK W. 2003: Fauna of the Socotra Archipelago. Field guide. Universitat Rostock, Rostock, 540 pp." type="book" year="2003">WRANIK (2003: 454)</bibRefCitation>
presents a photograph of a male of 
<taxonomicName box="[797,931,1227,1250]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Xylocopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="190" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[797,896,1227,1250]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="190">Xylocopa</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
from Hadiboh, which very likely represents 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1838" box="[423,563,1259,1282]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Xylocopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="190" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pubescens">
<emphasis box="[423,563,1259,1282]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="190">X. pubescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The species was often considered a synonym of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[113,236,1291,1314]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Xylocopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="190" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aestuans">
<emphasis box="[113,236,1291,1314]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="190">X. aestuans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the species significantly differ from each other (
<bibRefCitation author="LIEFTINCK M. A." box="[800,965,1291,1314]" pageId="7" pageNumber="190" pagination="137 - 158" refId="ref16146" refString="LIEFTINCK M. A. 1964: The identity of Apis aestuans Linne, 1758, and related Old World carpenter-bees (Xylocopa Latr.). Tijdschrift voor Entomologie 107: 137 - 158." type="journal article" year="1964">LIEFTINCK 1964</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="HANNAN M. A. &amp; ALQARNI A. S. &amp; OWAYSS A. A. &amp; ENGEL M. S." pageId="7" pageNumber="190" pagination="1 - 14" refId="ref15614" refString="HANNAN M. A., ALQARNI A. S., OWAYSS A. A. &amp; ENGEL M. S. 2012: The large carpenter bees of central Saudi Arabia, with notes on the biology of Xylocopa sulcatipes Maa (Hymenoptera, Apidae, Xylocopinae). ZooKeys 201: 1 - 14." type="journal article" year="2012">HANNAN et al. 2012</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="190" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="7.[113,1089,1227,1474]" pageId="7" pageNumber="190">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[113,260,1355,1378]" pageId="7" pageNumber="190">Distribution.</emphasis>
The species is widely distributed in Africa, 
<collectingCountry box="[715,791,1355,1378]" name="Turkey" pageId="7" pageNumber="190">Turkey</collectingCountry>
and eastwards to the eastern part of 
<collectingCountry box="[185,239,1387,1410]" name="India" pageId="7" pageNumber="190">India</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="ASCHER J. S. &amp; PICKERING J." box="[251,522,1387,1410]" pageId="7" pageNumber="190" refId="ref14368" refString="ASCHER J. S. &amp; PICKERING J. 2017: Discover Life bee species guide and world checklist (Hymenoptera: Apoidea: Anthophila). Available from: http: // www. discoverlife. org / mp / 20 q? guide = Apoidea _ species (April 26, 2017)." type="url" year="2017">ASCHER &amp; PICKERING 2017</bibRefCitation>
), but missing in southern parts of the Arabian Peninsula (
<bibRefCitation author="HANNAN M. A. &amp; ALQARNI A. S. &amp; OWAYSS A. A. &amp; ENGEL M. S." box="[121,330,1419,1442]" pageId="7" pageNumber="190" pagination="1 - 14" refId="ref15614" refString="HANNAN M. A., ALQARNI A. S., OWAYSS A. A. &amp; ENGEL M. S. 2012: The large carpenter bees of central Saudi Arabia, with notes on the biology of Xylocopa sulcatipes Maa (Hymenoptera, Apidae, Xylocopinae). ZooKeys 201: 1 - 14." type="journal article" year="2012">HANNAN et al. 2012</bibRefCitation>
). In 
<collectingCountry box="[374,455,1419,1442]" name="Yemen" pageId="7" pageNumber="190">Socotra</collectingCountry>
reported from Hadibu Plain, Goahal Gorge, Adho Dimellus (
<bibRefCitation author="KIRBY W. F." box="[121,250,1451,1474]" pageId="7" pageNumber="190" pagination="1898 - 9" refId="ref15844" refString="KIRBY W. F. 1903: Insecta: Hymenoptera. Pp. 235 - 258. In: FORBES H. O. (ed.): The natural history of Sokotra and Abd-el-Kuri: Being the report upon the results of the conjoint expedition to these islands in 1898 - 9. Special Bulletin of the Liverpool Museums, xlvii + 598 pp." type="book chapter" year="1903">KIRBY 1903</bibRefCitation>
), Ras Shoab (
<bibRefCitation author="KOHL F. F." box="[396,517,1451,1474]" pageId="7" pageNumber="190" refId="ref15911" refString="KOHL F. F. 1906: Zoologische Ergebnisse der Expedition der Kaiserlichen Akademie der Wissenschaften nach Sudarabien und Sokotra im Jahre 1898 - 1899. Hymenopteren. Kaiserlichen Akademie der Wissenschaften, Wien, 133 pp + XI pls. [Preprint of KOHL (1907)]." type="book" year="1906">KOHL 1906</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="KOHL F. F." box="[528,585,1451,1474]" pageId="7" pageNumber="190" pagination="169 - 301" refId="ref15961" refString="KOHL F. F. 1907: Zoologische Ergebnisse der Expedition der Kaiserlichen Akademie der Wissenschaften nach Sudarabien und Sokotra im Jahre 1898 - 1899. Hymenopteren. Denkschriften der Kaiserlichen Akademie der Wissenschaften, Mathematisch-Naturwissenschaftliche Klasse 71: 169 - 301 + pls I - XI." type="journal article" year="1907">1907</bibRefCitation>
), and Hadiboh (
<bibRefCitation author="WRANIK W." box="[755,905,1451,1474]" pageId="7" pageNumber="190" refId="ref17108" refString="WRANIK W. 2003: Fauna of the Socotra Archipelago. Field guide. Universitat Rostock, Rostock, 540 pp." type="book" year="2003">WRANIK 2003</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
